---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="HAX Principles - Vittorio's Portfolio">
  <section class="min-h-screen py-2000 px-400 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-600 text-tone-neutral-01">HAX Principles</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-tone-neutral-06 mb-1200 leading-relaxed">
        Designing transparent, predictable AI experiences following Microsoft HAX guidelines
      </p>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p class="text-tone-neutral-05 mb-800">
          Human-AI Experience (HAX) principles guide the design of AI systems that are
          transparent, predictable, and user-centered. These principles ensure AI enhances
          rather than hinders human capabilities.
        </p>
        
        <mds-card class="bg-label-green-10 mb-800">
          <mds-card-content>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-400 text-tone-neutral-01">Core HAX Principles</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-400 text-tone-neutral-05">
            <li>
              <strong>Make clear what the system can do</strong> - Users should understand
              the AI's capabilities and limitations.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Make clear how well the system can do what it can do</strong> -
              Provide confidence indicators and accuracy information.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Time services based on context</strong> - Deliver AI assistance
              at the right moment.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Show contextually relevant information</strong> - Present information
              that matters to the user's current task.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Match relevant social norms</strong> - Design AI interactions that
              feel natural and appropriate.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Mitigate social biases</strong> - Ensure AI systems are fair and
              inclusive.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Support efficient invocation</strong> - Make it easy for users to
              access AI features when needed.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Support efficient dismissal</strong> - Allow users to easily
              ignore or dismiss AI suggestions.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Support efficient correction</strong> - Enable users to fix AI
              mistakes quickly and easily.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Scope services when in doubt</strong> - Limit AI actions when
              uncertainty exists.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Make clear why the system did what it did</strong> - Provide
              explanations for AI decisions.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Remember recent interactions</strong> - Maintain context across
              user sessions.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Learn from user behavior</strong> - Adapt to user preferences
              over time.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Update and adapt cautiously</strong> - Make changes that improve
              rather than disrupt user workflows.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Encourage granular feedback</strong> - Enable users to provide
              specific feedback on AI performance.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Convey the consequences of user actions</strong> - Help users
              understand how their actions affect the AI system.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Provide global controls</strong> - Give users control over AI
              behavior and settings.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Notify users about changes</strong> - Keep users informed about
              system updates and changes.
            </li>
          </ul>
          </mds-card-content>
        </mds-card>
        
        <p class="text-tone-neutral-06">
          <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/haxtoolkit/ai-guidelines/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-label-green-04 hover:underline">
            Learn more about Microsoft HAX guidelines →
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-1200">
        <a href={baseUrl} class="text-label-green-04 hover:underline">← Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>


